-- Chilectra Says Customer Electricity Bills to Fall Average 8.6%
-- B y   S e b a s t i a n   B o y d
-- 2012-03-20T13:03:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/chilectra-says-customer-electricity-bills-to-fall-average-8-6-.html
Chilectra SA (CHILECTR) , a Chilean power
distribution, said its customers’ bills will fall an average 8.6
percent in coming months as it applies lower electricity node
prices.  The lower prices affect to all bills since Jan. 1 and the
company, which supplies power to 1.6 million clients in the
Santiago region, will apply a discount to bills in April.  Chilectra is 99 percent owned by  Enersis SA (ENERSIS) , the Latin
American unit of  Spain ’s  Endesa SA. (ELE)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Sebastian Boyd in Santiago at 
 sboyd9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
